\name{ggdecompose}
\alias{ggdecompose}
\alias{ggobserve}
\alias{ggtrend}
\alias{ggseason}
\alias{ggrandom}
\alias{ggdetrend}
\alias{ggdeseason}
\title{
Visualisation of Decomposed Time Series
}
\description{
These functions plots the observed, trend, seasonal, and random components of time series into one figure (ggdecompose) or into separate figures (ggobserve, ggtrend, ggseason, ggrandom, respectively). These functions also plots detrended and deseasonalised time series (ggdetrend and ggseason, respectively). These can be integrated with ggplot functions.
}
\usage{
ggdecompose(x)
ggobserve(x)
ggtrend(x)
ggseason(x)
ggrandom(x)
ggdetrend(x)
ggdeseason(x)
}

%- maybe also 'usage' for other objects documented here.
